article.headline: Quinnipiac 74, St. Francis, N.Y. 72
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. (AP) -- DeMario Anderson had 21 points and three steals as Quinnipiac held off St. Francis of New York for a 74-72 win Thursday night. Allan Sheppard had 19 points and 12 rebounds for St. Francis, which scored the final 13 points of the game. Both teams went scoreless in the final 2 minutes. A potential game-winning 3-point attempt at the buzzer by Robert Hines of St. Francis missed its mark. Van Crafton finished with 15 points for Quinnipiac (6-10), which was playing its final men's game at the Burt Kahn Court. The Bobcats move into the new TD Banknorth Sports Center on Jan. 27. The Terriers (3-16) trailed by 19 at the half but shot 55 percent in the second half to charge back. Hines finished with 16 point for St. Francis and Jamal Womack added 12.
